Let $\displaystyle R$ be the finite region bounded above by the curve

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle y = 4 - x^{2}
\end{align*} and bounded below by

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle y = 2-x.
\end{align*} Express the volume of the solid obtained by
rotating $\displaystyle R$ about the vertical line $\displaystyle x = 2$
as a definite integral. You do not need to simplify or evaluate this
integral.
